Atriplex halimus

   [3546.jpg]
    Authority   L.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Caryophyllidae:Caryophyllales:Chenopodiaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3546

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Malcolm C 1969 [SAL, DRA, TEXT, RAIN, DEP]
   Houerou H 1971 pp 16 21 [RAIN, KTMP]
   B-Lennard E 1984 pp 155 [SAL, DRA, KTMP]
   White F 1983 pp 229 [SAL, RAIN, KTMP]
   Aronson J 1989 pp 54 [SAL]
   National AS 1975 pp 125 [DEP, DRA, RAIN, SAL, USE]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial shrub.
   COMMON NAMES
   Mediterranean sal.
   FURTHER INF
   Mediterranean sal is native of the Mediterranean region. A very hardy
   species, but not very palatable. It can be grown on slopes. The
   water-table should be less than 3-10 m below the surface.
   Photosynthesis pathway C4. A 3-5 years old stand can produce 1-4 t/ha
   of dry matter with 150-170 mm of annual rainfall.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
